&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facilities Domestic Cleaning Supervisor – Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Supervisor looking for an exciting new challenge? We might have the role for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facilities Services is part of the Estates and Facilities Directorate, delivering in-house soft FM services within Nottinghamshire Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust, across Nottinghamshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Supervisor looking for an exciting new challenge? We might have the role for you! We have a vacancy for a Facilities Supervisor working at Wells Road Centre DMH &amp; COMMUNITY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone to supervise domestic staff and oversee their cleaning duties to ensure cleanliness standards are maintained. We require someone with a passion for delivering a quality service. Shifts patterns are between the hours of 7am and 7pm on a rota which includes weekends and Bank Holidays. Applicants must be flexible and able to work additional shifts as and when required. As a Supervisor, you will be responsible for ensuring that Health &amp; Safety legislation is adhered to at all times. You will also have a key role in staff management and budget control.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full UK driving licence and vehicle for business use is required for this post; however reasonable adjustments will be made for disabled individuals in line with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact Claire Teft, Senior Supervisor on claire.teft@nottshc.nhs.uk or 0115 9691300 EXT 13797&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
